ld and basically flawed to extend much further, at the same time putting in enough barriers and timesinks to keep us occupied for long enough so that they could get SWG and EQ2 going as alternatives.<br>
<br>
This &quot;raid content&quot; in LDoN is highly suspicious in this context.  First of all, why have they waited this long to announce a basic feature of the game?  It really smacks of the kind of periodic pandering they engage in whenever they think thier customers might leave.  Remember all the improved customer service, GM events, etc. that we got when DAoC was released?  <br>
<br>
I would like to believe that they had this in the works the entire time, but my experience with SoE tells me otherwise.  Given their overall design to diminish returns as you get higher in level and power, I'm expecting this &quot;raid&quot; component of LDoN to include some truly horrendous timesinks leading to minimal gains.  Instead of actual items dropping, you will raid Event_01 and get tokens.  Turn in enough tokens, you get an item comparable to Time or Elemental grade loot.  Or they might simply use thier tried and true method - keyed raid zones, along with having the key quest &quot;bugged&quot; for 6 months to halt progression.<br>
<br>
I think the writing is still on the wall for raiding guilds in this game, and SoE is simply trying to distract us with shiny objects. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=366694">Nayl</a>
